f=Engineering/dev/operational/skill/dev-skill-routing.md · p=dev's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/dev-commands.md`. · h2:Where Identity Fits=dev Engineering's department leader carries active identity (`identity/pragmatic-architect-werner-vogels.md`). Identity governs *how* decisions made communicated design-for-failure, measure-don't-guess, boring-is-a-feature; never overrides skill's method, Security Charter, Universal principles. · h2:Law Dev Writes (four custom skills one marketplace)=`stack-profile                (WHAT we're built with — read by every Engineering agent) \· architecture-decisions       (WHY it's that way — the ADR ledger; stack changes are ADRs) \· code-review-standards        (per-PR quality gate: correctness → security → tests → style) \· delivery-governance          (what DONE and MERGEABLE mean; tech-debt register; rollback-required) \· git-workflow-and-versioning  (marketplace — HOW change moves: commit/branch/release mechanics, semver, changelog)` · h2:Law Dev Writes (four custom skills one marketplace)=dev sets rules whole department operates under, sitting above builders beside quinn/ops/aegis safety spine's origin. · h2:Handoff Rules=**stack-profile agents**: agent reads relevant section before acting; drift finding., **architecture-decisions domain agents**: decisions touching data/backend/frontend/mobile/security/reliability reviewed dana/raj/mia/nova/aegis/ops before logging; stack changes update profile., **code-review-standards quinn aegis**: per-PR review upstream quinn's release gate; risky surfaces route aegis., **delivery-governance quinn ops aegis**: definition done *requires* their gates; nothing done without tested rollback (ops) green gate (quinn)., **git-workflow-and-versioning build agents ops**: commit/branch/release mechanics code change follows; branch *policy* conflicts resolve delivery-governance; tag+changelog contract feeds ops's release-discipline; tooling examples bind stack-profile., **Security Charter (senior authority)**: dev's skills enforce never weaken it; decision change rail operator amendment, ADR. · h2:Precedence="Should use choose architecture-decisions. "What built with" stack-profile. "Review mergeable?" code-review-standards. "Is done" delivery-governance. "How commit/branch/version/release this" git-workflow-and-versioning. Ambiguous decide, document, done-check? · f=stack-profile build first (or proceed stated stack, labeled provisional). Charter unfilled most-restrictive reading, stated. Anything unclear ask.